last_episode_to_air.overview: It's rookie Savannah's first time dispatching July fourth. While she leans on her team's years of experience, thereâ€™s no telling what's to come. When a drunk driver takes off on Savannah's officers, she must come to grips with a tragic outcome.

name: 911 Crisis Center
overview: An up-close and personal look at a team of 911 dispatchers at a call center just outside of Cleveland where they take on a never-ending bombardment of panic-stricken callers and save lives.

episodes.name: 12 Hours Together
episodes.overview: 911 Dispatcher, Essence Sullins, and the night shift team field non-stop emergency calls from 7pm-6am, including one that connects to someone in Essence's family.

episodes.name: Best of Luck
episodes.overview: On her last shift at CVD, veteran 911 dispatcher Christine Mazzeo must navigate the chaos of St. Patrick's Day and say goodbye to the work-family she's been with through thick and thin over 12 years.

episodes.name: Training Wheels
episodes.overview: 911 Dispatch Trainee Matt Reinke is almost through the training program at CVD, but before he graduates, he must prove his ability to successfully navigate the night shift, the callers, and his fellow dispatchers.

episodes.name: Octopus Mode
episodes.overview: Supervisor Charline Polk leans on her 16 years of experience to handle crisis after crisis, but when she answers the phone to an open line and screaming in the background, she is faced with a situation that chills her the bone.

episodes.name: Third Time's the Charm
episodes.overview: Nancy ties the knot. But first, the team must piece together the puzzle of a possible kidnapping. The dispatchers are interrupted during the Wedding Livestream when they hear police call out someone's been shot.

episodes.name: 40 Shots Fired
episodes.overview: Dispatcher Melanie McCavish and the team ramp up into all hands on deck when a barrage of shots fired calls come in at the same time, including a call from the person who's been shot.

episodes.name: What To Expect
episodes.overview: 911 Dispatcher Abby Encarnacion is pregnant with her first child and must navigate working 12-hour shifts, taking highly emotional calls, and instructing CPR to a mother who discovers her son is unresponsive.

episodes.name: Put To the Test
episodes.overview: It's dispatcher Marra Wargo's first week in her new position as Supervisor. Despite handling lifelong anxiety, she leads the team through a storm of emergencies, panicked witnesses, and a dog in danger.

episodes.name: Teamwork Makes the Dream Work
episodes.overview: 911 Dispatcher Jackie Chappuies takes training rookie Hayley Kilbane into her own hands. Together they face back-to-back carjackings at the same gas station and a possible overdose that calls for immediate CPR, which Hayley has never instructed before...

episodes.name: Double Homicide
episodes.overview: Supervisor Christine "Mooch" Muccino drives the shift through a series of crises including a fatal car accident and a horrific shooting in broad daylight, but nothing shakes her to the core more than when she learns of a crisis at home.

episodes.name: They're Out There
episodes.overview: The dispatchers at CVD brace for Full Moon madness. All hell breaks loose throughout the night when a traffic stop turns into a full-blown pursuit, strange lights in the sky are seen, and a major accident leaves a motorcyclist motionless.

episodes.name: Help Is on the Way
episodes.overview: The shift comes together to support their pregnant teammate, Kaitlyn Schroeder, when she takes a call reporting two kids shot in the face, and a caller whose childbirth doesn't go exactly to plan.

episodes.name: The First, First Responders
episodes.overview: It's the best time of the year for the dispatchers; dispatcher appreciation week officially begins, and while morale isÂ high, the crime rate seems to be higher; night shift is going to have to get creative to sort out a mess of emergencies.

episodes.name: Appreciation in Action
episodes.overview: Dispatch Appreciation Week is in full swing, raffle tickets are flowing, costumes are aplenty, and prizes will be won.

episodes.name: Positive Impacts
episodes.overview: Jessica Merkosky taps into her cheerleader past to raise her teamâ€™s spirits and battle the heaviness of 911 calls. Her coworker Tiffany Ward, also takes on an emotionally-charged night when they each answer calls from families in a similar crisis.

episodes.name: Work Family
episodes.overview: The team comes together to support Donna Majoros when sheâ€™s faced with a call that brings a past trauma into light. When Essence takes a break, a carjacking goes from bad to worse. Melinda caps off another night at dispatch with a cake with a twist!

episodes.name: Mama Bear to Grizzly Bear
episodes.overview: Supervisor Charline Polk is known as the Mama Bear of Chagrin Valley Dispatch; when she takes a 911 call from a concerned grandfather looking for his missing 2-week-old grandchild, Charline and the team combine forces to unravel the mystery.

episodes.name: Matt on the Move
episodes.overview: Matt Reinke has learned the ins and outs of dispatching and is ready to apply for supervisor; he must help a young girl threatened with a knife and a panicked caller with a baby struggling to breathe.

episodes.name: Irish Moon
episodes.overview: It's a double whammy at dispatch when St. Patrick's Day falls on a Full Moon. Charline takes matters into her own hands when she hears a couple screaming over an open line, and the night shift tries to track down a man who reports he's been shot.

episodes.name: Momivisor
episodes.overview: Abby navigates being a new mom in a new supervisor; as she oversees the room, her skills are tested when a welfare check spirals into a pursuit; when reports of a juvenile with gunshot wounds come in, Abby faces a mother's worst nightmare.

episodes.name: Dispatch Dad
episodes.overview: Rookie Steve Schieferstein is new to CVD but brings a wealth of experience as a former EMT in police officer; for 12 hours straight, Steve must adjust to the other side of the phone and handle all types of calls â€” from roadkill to a full arrest.

episodes.name: Supernatural Woman
episodes.overview: Melinda Pilat is a bona fide believer in aliens and Bigfoot, thanks to her late father; leaning on his memory, she handles the horrors of a house on fire with dogs still inside and a color and distress who discovers her nephew unresponsive.

episodes.name: A Week to Be Appreciated
episodes.overview: The shift is showered with food and fun during Appreciation Week, but the calls keep coming, including a robbery in real time and reports from the gruesome scene of an accident; dispatcher Tiffany Ward wins an award for a call from the previous year.

episodes.name: Pins, Prizes and Dispatch Pride
episodes.overview: As Dispatch Week winds down, Essence keeps her eye on the prize; Charline and Melanie help a caller track down a cat burglar; dispatcher Jennifer Barber struggles to get a caller to start CPR before it's too late, earning herself a lifesaver pin.

episodes.name: Leaving a Legacy
episodes.overview: Dispatcher Arnold Rinas taps into his 15 years of experience to prepare the new trainees for the job; he helps newbie Salena Hall navigate 911 and must deescalate a dangerous dispute when a neighbor pulls a gun on the caller and her family.

episodes.name: Close Call
episodes.overview: A year after dispatcher Donna Majoros took the 911 call before her mother passed, she leans on her best friend, Melinda, more than ever; Abby answers a call from an address connected to Donna, and her day goes from bad to worse.

episodes.name: Cheers to Saving Lives
episodes.overview: Jessica Merkosky keeps spirits high on the dispatch floor while her shift scrambles to make sense of a reported gunshot victim in the drive-thru lane; when Jessica coaches a caller through CPR on his mother, she's shocked to learn the cause.

episodes.name: The Loop
episodes.overview: Jennifer Barber is thriving in her first year dispatching at CVD, but when she gets caught in a never-ending cycle of calls involving children, she must lean on her team to help every caller.

episodes.name: Police Week
episodes.overview: The team honors their partners and is reminded of the danger police face daily; Savannah Brown, the youngest dispatcherÂ at CVD, is eager to prove herself in front of her experienced colleagues.

episodes.name: Friday the 13th Part 911
episodes.overview: When the dispatchers discover the last day of Police Week falls on Friday the 13th, some embrace the strange, while others struggle to find the humor through a shift of bizarre calls involving snakes, surfers and an unexpected seizure.

episodes.name: Mother of a Day
episodes.overview: Shift supervisors Laura and Charline try their best to celebrate moms working on Mother's Day. When a flood of calls come in to report a horrific shooting in the open, Essence reflects on the importance of her family both in and outside of work.

episodes.name: The Officer's Wife
episodes.overview: Dispatcher Savannah Brown settles in at CVD thanks to the support from her police officer spouse, but while helping callers in threatening situations with little information to relay to police, she fears she is sending them blindly into danger.

episodes.name: Memorial Day Weekend
episodes.overview: The dispatchers brace for non-stop 911 calls as Memorial Day weekend ends with chaos; while the team handles a householdÂ shooting and a pursuit that becomes a standoff, supervisor Charline notices one of her own hasn't shown up and fears the worst.

episodes.name: It's Always Darkest Before It's Dawn
episodes.overview: With only 24 hours to go before Memorial Day finally ends, Charline and the team's determination is put to the ultimateÂ test after days of life-and-death emergencies; it all comes to a head when an officer chasing a suspect goes silent.

episodes.name: Me and the Trainee
episodes.overview: The pressure is on Jessica and new trainee Patrick when a panicked woman calls 911 for her unresponsive boyfriend; whileÂ Jessica gets CPR started, Patrick is on his own to dispatch the rescue squad before it's too late.

episodes.name: Supervisor Matt
episodes.overview: On Matt's first day as supervisor, he must navigate his new duties while leading the team that trained him just one yearÂ ago; anxieties spike when a caller learns of a possible hostage situation; reports of a house fire call for rapid action.

episodes.name: Fireworks
episodes.overview: With July 4th just around the corner, the dispatchers brace for nonstop complaints and hope for the best. When a block party breaks out in a fight, the dispatchers scramble to get the officers the details they need before it turns deadly.
